{
  "texts": [
    "To maintain fairness and robustness, identical parameters were applied across the experiments on the same ProText dataset and encoder.",
    "The evaluated approaches included traditional neural networks, pre-trained language models, and graph-based neural networks.",
    "To comprehensively evaluate our proposed method for semi-supervised short-text classification, we compared it with the following nine state-of-the-art methods: Text Convolutional Neural Network (TCNN) 14 and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) 63:",
    "• LSTM 63 uses the last hidden state as the representation of the whole text.",
    "We also experimented with the model and with without pretrained word embeddings."
  ]
}